# 
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "High-risk medical devices, typically those that support or sustain life, are implanted, or present a potential significant risk of illness or injury."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/ClassIII> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Class III"@en .
# 
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/IVDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Regulation (EU) 2017/746 of the European Parliament and of the Council on in vitro diagnostic medical devices and repealing Directive 98/79/EC and Commission Decision 2010/227/EU."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/IVDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR (In Vitro Diagnostic Medical Devices Regulation)"@en .
# 
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Device that can be inserted inside the human body."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/ImplantableActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Active Device"@en .
# 
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of physical trauma or damage to the human body associated with device operation or failure."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Injury Risk"@en .
# 
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/MDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Regulation (EU) 2017/745 of the European Parliament and of the Council on medical devices, amending Directive 2001/83/EC, Regulation (EC) No 178/2002 and Regulation (EC) No 1223/2009."@en .
<http://www.semanticweb.org/migue/ontologies/MedicalDevicesOntology/MDR> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MDR (Medical Device Regulation)"@en .
